						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Date lost</hi></p>						

						<p>Badly damaged. Contains the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇadēvarāya</hi> describing his victories. Seems to record an endowment of lands in the villages Muttarasanallūr, Peruṅguḍi, etc., as well as a gift of some jewels set with precious stones. The date of the record is lost. On a comparison of the contents of the record with No. 371 above it is possible to surmise that the record may be placed about 1517 A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
